<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which Progressive Era federal agency was established FIRST?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The Federal Reserve System</option>
            <option letter="b">The Department of Commerce and Labor</option>
            <option letter="c">The Federal Trade Commission</option>
            <option letter="d">The Department of Labor</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Department of Commerce and Labor was established first, created under Theodore Roosevelt's administration in 1903. The Federal Reserve System and Department of Labor (which split from Commerce) were both created under Wilson in 1913, while the Federal Trade Commission was established in 1914. The chronological order reflects the growing federal regulation of business and labor during the Progressive Era.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
